<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870326-0003 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Chubb Corp.</HL><DD> 03/26/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CB </IN><TEXT>   CHUBB CORP. asked shareholders to limit the circumstances in which directors and officers of the Warrren, N.J.-based insurer may be personally liable for damages related to breach of their duties. The proposal, scheduled for a vote at the annual meeting April 21, would also provide for Chubb to idemnify those individuals against certain liabilities and legal expenses. The proposed changes to the company's certificate of incorporation, similar to those being made by many corporations, follow a February modification of New Jersey corporate law. </TEXT></DOC>